          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and recitation and is a post-Vedic upaniṣad, a philosophical treatise written in verse containing mantras and told through a narrative/mythological allegory, focusing on the centrality of the Hindu god Śiva as the highest principle in the universe and identifying him with the gods Viṣṇu, Brahmā, and Indra.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kaivalyopaniṣad</title>
              <title type="vernacular">कैवल्योपनिषद्</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Śaktiyukta Vināyaka Sahasrabudhi</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti kaivalyopaniṣat cicchaktiyuktena vināyakena sahasrabudhyupanāmake tadehena likhitā // śake 1742 āṣāṭavadhacaturdaśyāṃ jñānadātāsomaḥ prīyatāṃ // samāptaḥ //</colophon>
